# Sokolovka, Sterlitamaksky District, Republic of Bashkortostan

}}
Sokolovka () is a rural locality (a village) in Pervomaysky Selsoviet, Sterlitamaksky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 160 as of 2010. There is 1 street.
Geography
Sokolovka is located 46 km northwest of Sterlitamak (the district's administrative centre) by road. Dergachevka is the nearest rural locality.
